{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ice}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Beartic}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ice|prevnum=613|prev=Cubchoo|nextnum=615|next=Cryogonal|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Beartic}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Beartic\n|jname=ツンベアー\n|jtranslit=Tsunbeā\n|tmname=Tunbear\n|category=Freezing\n|type1=Ice\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Snow Cloak\n|ability2=Slush Rush\n|abilityd=Swift Swim\n|ndex=614\n|udex=120\n|u2dex=196\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=082\n|height-ftin=8\'06"\n|height-m=2.6\n|weight-lbs=573.2\n|weight-kg=260.0\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|expyield=177<!--170 in Gen V-VI-->\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=White\n|catchrate=60\n|evtotal=2\n|evat=2\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=beartic\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Beartic\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ツンベアー\'\'\' \'\'Tunbear\'\') is an {{type|Ice}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Cubchoo}} starting at [[level]] 37.\n\n==Biology==\nBeartic is an ursine, quadruped Pokémon capable of standing on its hind legs. It has bluish white fur with a shaggy tuft at its rear. Three spikes of ice hang from its lower jaw, forming a beard. Its face consists of a long snout, beady black eyes, and rounded ears. Its large forepaws have black claws and paw pads. Beartic is capable of freezing its own breath, and will create pathways across water using this technique. It inhabits northern areas where it catches prey in the cold waters.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Morgan Beartic.png|thumb|250px|Beartic in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===In the main series===\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Georgia\'s Beartic]]=====\nBeartic debuted in \'\'[[BW033|Iris and Excadrill Against the Dragon Buster!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Georgia]]. It was first used in Georgia\'s {{pkmn|battle}} against {{an|Iris}}. It easily managed to defeat {{TP|Iris|Axew}}, as well as {{TP|Iris|Excadrill}}. It was later challenged to a [[rematch]], where it tied against Excadrill.\n\n=====Other=====\nMultiple {{pkmn2|wild}} Beartic appeared in \'\'[[BW046|The Beartic Mountain Feud!]]\'\', where they played a major role.\n\nA Beartic appeared in \'\'[[BW078|Guarding the Guardian of the Mountain!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Brycen]]. It reappeared in \'\'[[BW079|Caution: Icy Battle Conditions!]]\'\', as Brycen\'s third and final Pokémon in his [[Gym]] battle with {{Ash}}. Beartic reappeared again in a flashback in \'\'[[BW103|Certain Up, Unova League!]]\'\'.\n\nA wild Beartic appeared in \'\'[[BW088|The Mystery of the Missing Cubchoo!]]\'\'. It was briefly mistaken as {{OBP|Chris|BW088}}\'s {{p|Cubchoo}}, which they thought had evolved. However, this was proven wrong when Chris couldn\'t recall it into a Poké Ball.\n\nA Beartic appeared in \'\'[[BW112|Team Plasma\'s Pokémon Power Plot!]]\'\' as a test specimen of [[Colress]]\'s. It was used to fight {{AP|Pikachu}} and {{TP|Iris|Axew}}. It was eventually released from Colress\'s control when {{TRT}} stole his computer\'s data.\n\nA Beartic appeared in \'\'[[BW134|The Journalist from Another Region!]]\'\', under the ownership of {{OBP|Morgan|BW134}}. It was used in a battle against Iris, where it took on {{TP|Iris|Dragonite}} and won when Dragonite was disqualified. Another Beartic appeared during a flashback explaining the history of the [[Pokémon Sumo Tournament]] on [[Harvest Island]].\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA group of Beartic appeared in the prologue of \'\'[[M14|Black—Victini and Reshiram]]\'\'. They lived on the frozen tundra where the village that [[Glacine]], [[Luis]], [[Donuke]], and other People of the Vale lived in was located. They were seen lingering on an ice shelf when a giant glacier collided with the ice, agitating them.\n\nA Beartic appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[BW043|Meowth\'s Scrafty Tactics!]]\'\', where it was one of the Pokémon a wild {{p|Scrafty}} tried to recruit in an effort to reclaim its den.\n\nA Beartic appeared as a silhouette in \'\'[[BW047|Crisis from the Underground Up!]]\'\'.\n\nA Beartic appeared in \'\'[[M15|Kyurem VS. The Sword of Justice]]\'\' during the {{OBP|Swords of Justice|M15}} legend.\n\nA Beartic appeared in a fantasy in \'\'[[BW120|Ash and N: A Clash of Ideals!]]\'\'.\n\nA Beartic appeared in a fantasy or a flashback in \'\'[[BW134|The Journalist from Another Region!]]\'\'.\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW033|Beartic|Ash\'s Pokédex|Beartic, the Freezing Pokémon. Beartic\'s frozen breath can create fangs and claws made of ice. It lives in frigid northern areas.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n===In Pokémon Generations===\n[[File:Brycen Beartic PG.png|thumb|250px|Beartic in [[Pokémon Generations]]]]\n[[Brycen]]\'s Beartic appeared in \'\'[[PG13|The Uprising]]\'\'.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Brycen Beartic Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Beartic in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Be the Best! Pokémon B+W manga===\n[[Cheren]] was seen with a Beartic in \'\'[[PBW8|The Birth of the Best Pokémon Trainer!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA {{tc|Team Plasma Grunt}} used a Beartic to battle {{adv|Black}} and {{adv|Cheren}} inside the [[Cold Storage]] in \'\'[[PS491|Fight in a Cold Climate]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Beartic appeared in \'\'[[PS489|Drawing Bridges]]\'\'.\n\nIn \'\'[[PS499|School of Hard Knocks]]\'\', [[Brycen]]\'s Beartic was used in the Gym battle against Black to conclude his training. It was defeated by Black\'s [[Costa]].\n\nA Beartic appeared in a flashback as one of the Pokémon trained by the [[International Police]] in \'\'[[PS528|Innocent Scientist]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon + Nobunaga\'s Ambition ~ Ranse\'s Color Picture Scroll ~ manga===\nA Beartic appeared in \'\'[[PNA4|The Scarlet Scroll: Kunoichi\'s Situation]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon RéBURST 