ination of \'\'bear\'\', or possibly \'\'beard\'\', and \'\'{{wp|arctic}}\'\'. Notably, \'\'arctic\'\' itself derives from ἄρκτος \'\'arktos\'\', Ancient Greek for \'\'bear\'\'.\n\nTunbear may be a combination of \'\'{{wp|tundra}}\'\', 氷柱 \'\'tsurara\'\' (icicle), and \'\'bear\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Ice|type2=Ice\n|ja=ツンベアー \'\'Tunbear\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'tundra\'\', {{tt|氷柱 \'\'tsurara\'\'|icicle}} and \'\'bear\'\'\n|fr=Polagriffe|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|polaire|polar}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|griffe|claw}}\'\'\n|es=Beartic|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Siberio|demeaning=From \'\'{{wp|Siberia}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|Bär|bear}}\'\'\n|it=Beartic|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=툰베어 \'\'Tunbear\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=凍原熊 / 冻原熊 \'\'Dòngyuánxióng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "Tundra bear"\n|ru=Бертик \'\'Bertik\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Georgia\'s Beartic]]\n<!--\n==Notes==\n<references />-->\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ice}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ice|prevnum=613|prev=Cubchoo|nextnum=615|next=Cryogonal}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Pokémon whose base stats changed in Generation VII]]\n\n[[de:Siberio]]\n[[es:Beartic]]\n[[fr:Polagriffe]]\n[[it:Beartic]]\n[[ja:ツンベアー]]\n[[zh:冻原熊]]'}